Moorsfang, I guess your guild must not care about you very much.  That's the only way that I can figure that you could tell them, &quot;hey, I'm online but I don't feel like talking to any of you&quot; and not have 15 people asking you what's wrong.  In contrast, if I say something like that, I do have a number of people sending me tells, trying to cheer me up, trying to find out what's bugging me.  Sometimes you don't want that, though.  Sometimes you just want to ... gasp ... be alone.<br>
<br>
I'm not afraid of backlash because I'm doing my own thing.  Then again, I'd never choose &quot;doing my own thing&quot; over raiding with my guild unless I had to, as I do right now because my connection can't withstand raids.   It's lonely to see all of the fun stuff going on without being able to participate.  Hence why I'm rarely online when there's guild stuff going on -- it's just too depressing. <p><TABLE ALIGN="left" width="25%">
